<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9985> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9985" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph de Poeneis. MRR I.207, Itgenshorst no. 130, Rich no. 129." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1135> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1135" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Returned from Sicily when succeeded by Atilius, and celebrated as Procos. a triumph over the Carthaginians (Act. Tr., Degrassi 76f., 548; cf. Zon. 8.11)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1131> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1131" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap. (names entire); Eutrop. 2.20; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Oros. 4.7.11; Cassiod.; and on Scipio, CIL 1\n     .2.8 and 9- ILS 2 and 3; Liv. Per. 17; Degrassi 42f., 115, 434f. Scipio with the fleet attacked Sardinia and Corsica and captured Aleria (CIL and ILS, as above; Act. Tr.; Liv. Per. 17; Val. Max. 5.1.2; Sil. Ital. 6.671ff.; Frontin. Str. 3.9.4, and 10.2; Flor. 1.18.15-16; Oros. 4.7.11-12; Zon. 8.11; cf. Polyb. 1.24.5-8). He celebrated a triumph over Carthaginians, Sardinia and Corsica (Act. Tr., Degrassi 76f., 548; Eutrop. 2.20), and dedicated a temple to the Tempestates (CIL and ILS, as above; cf. Ov. Fast. 6.193f.). Aquillius held command in Sicily against Hamilcar Barca (Zon. 8.11; cf. Polyb. 1.24.8)." .
